Project Coriolis are recruiting participants for the study Ã¢â‚¬Å“Multi-Modal Interaction Research and Simulator Development". Participants will be able to have a VR experience in ts experiment. There will be two sessions, the first session will last for approximately 2 hours and the second session will last for approximately 1 hour. You will be reimbursed $15/hour in cash vouchers for your participation. 



These are our criteria:  

*	Age 18 and above; 
*	Normal/Corrected-to-normal vision; 
*	Not using bifocal/trifocal/progressive lenses; 
*	Have not undergone corneal (e.g lasik, prk) surgery; 
*	No cataract or intraocular implants; 
*	No eye movement/alignment abnormalities (e.g lazy eye, strabismus, nystagmus)



The information received will be kept confidential and used strictly for academic publications only. Identifiable information will never be revealed. Further information on ts research study is found in the attached Participant Information Sheet and Consent Form (PIS&CF). 



